<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2006] JDK Dynamic Proxies Broken</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2006</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Groovy beans wrapped in JDK style proxies throw an &quot;IllegalArgumentException: object is not an instance of declaring class&quot; when a method is called on them from a Groovy object.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thread on subject from the dev list: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/JDK-Style-Proxy-Issue-tf4137792.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/JDK-Style-Proxy-Issue-tf4137792.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Diagnosis from Jochen Theodorou: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Re%3A-JDK-Style-Proxy-Issue-p11815320.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Re%3A-JDK-Style-Proxy-Issue-p11815320.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
